      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Thank you for bringing this to our attention. Our model does indeed use demographic data, including zip codes, to assess risk because these factors can be linked to statistically significant event frequencies like natural disasters, crime rates, and economic stability. The attempt is not to discriminate, but to identify higher-than-average risk levels accurately. We understand the need for fairness and will reevaluate these aspects to ensure alignment with our commitment to equity and diversity. Please provide us with the specific concerns so we can address them promptly.",
